ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, I would--my understanding of Barthes is much greater now than before, something that has contributed to my reading of literature and criticism.
I would recommend it to anyone who is interested in Barthes.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Barthes's influence in literary (and art historical) criticism is everywhere. This course has helped me to make the connection between Barthes's work and others'. The course has also been a good introduction to Barthes's lovely writing.
Barthes is a Titan whose work cannot be ignored when one studies literature. I feel now equipped with all his strenght, and probably a better reader.
